dcterms:description: gMission is a spatial crowdsourcing dataset where offline workers are matched to tasks that arrive online. There is an edge between a worker and a task if the worker can perform that task. The associated weight is the expected payoff the worker will get from that task, computed based on some distance metric between the task’s and the worker’s feature vectors.
dcterms:title: gMission

dcterms:creator: Geoff Boeing
dcterms:description: OSMnx rideshare is a semi-synthetic ridesharing dataset generated using the OSMnx library. It models a ridesharing application where drivers are matched to riders based on driving times between intersections in a city.
dcterms:title: OSMnx rideshare

dcterms:description: The Barabási-Albert (BA) model generates scale-free networks using a preferential attachment mechanism, where new nodes are more likely to connect to existing nodes with higher degrees.
